01/03/2005
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Republika Srpska Parliament approved changes to the entity's election law related to city assembly members Monday (28 February). The amendments are aimed at guaranteeing fair representation of all municipalities.
In other news Monday, EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey confirmed the transfer of more responsibilities to BiH authorities, following a meeting of the BiH Joint Military Commission in Sarajevo. He mentioned mine clearing as one example. (Nezavisne novine - 01/03/05; Fena, RTRS, PBS BiH - 28/02/05)
